eu.itesla_project.iidm.network

Interface Network

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Identifiable

    public interface Network
extends Identifiable
    A power network model.

    To create a new network, use NetworkFactory.

    The network is initially created with one state identified by StateManager.INITIAL_STATE_ID. StateManager is responsible for state management and is accessible from the network thanks to getStateManager().

    Instances of Network are not thread safe except for attributes depending of the state (always specified in the javadoc) if StateManager.allowStateMultiThreadAccess(boolean) is set to true.

    Author:
    Geoffroy Jamgotchian
    See Also:
    NetworkFactory, StateManager
